      "raw_text": "T A description of the prisoner was\ntelegraphed to different cities\nwhich resulted in his being identi-\nfed as Harry Orchard, the man\ncharged with having blown up the\nrailroad depot at independence,\nColo, on the morning OF June G.,\n1904. in which 13 men were killed\nand as many more injured for life.\n! Orchard was a prominent mem\nDer of the Western Federation of\nMiners during the great Cripple\nCreek strike in 1904, disappearing\nImmediately after the Independ.\nence depot disaster He was a\nleading agitator during the riots\nFollowing the strike of the miners\nat Occur d'Alene, when the shaft\nhouse and mill of the Bunker Hill\nsullivan mine were wrecked by an\n| explosion of dynamite\n\n\nThe general belief is that Gov.\n\n\nSteunenberg was assassinated for\nsending the state militia to Occur\nd'Alene and quelllng the riots, at\nwhich time many miners were con-\nfined in the bull pen\" established\nat his direction."
